@startuml
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

participant "Kubelet" as K
participant "Device Plugin\n(DaemonSet Pod)" as DP
participant "API Server" as API
participant "kube-scheduler" as SCH
actor "User" as U

== Node Startup: Kubelet Prepares Registration Service ==

note over K
  ① Start Registration gRPC service
  Create kubelet.sock (Unix Socket)
  Path: /var/lib/kubelet/device-plugins/kubelet.sock
end note

== Device Plugin Starts and Registers ==

note over DP
  ② Device Plugin Pod starts
  Mount host kubelet.sock into container
end note

DP -> K : ③ Register(endpoint, version, resourceName)\nvia kubelet.sock
K --> DP : Registration successful

== Device Discovery and Resource Reporting ==

K -> DP : ④ ListAndWatch()\nvia Device Plugin's Unix Socket
DP --> K : Return device list [{ID, Health}, ...]\n(continuously listen for device add/remove events)

K -> API : ⑤ Update Node status\nNode.status.capacity[nvidia.com/gpu] = 1

== User Submits Pod ==

U -> API : ⑥ Create Pod\n(resources.limits: nvidia.com/gpu: 1)
API -> SCH : Notify pending Pod
SCH -> SCH : ⑦ Filter nodes meeting resource requirements
SCH -> API : Bind result (write Pod.spec.nodeName)

== Device Allocation and Container Start ==

API -> K : Notify pending Pod on this node
K -> DP : ⑧ Allocate(deviceIDs)
DP --> K : Return allocation result\n(device file paths, env vars, etc.)

note over K
  ⑨ Start container, inject device info
  Mount /dev/nvidia0
  Inject NVIDIA_VISIBLE_DEVICES
end note

@enduml
